The sentence "they \_\_\_ out just now" is not complete and requires a verb to be grammatically correct. Without more context, it's hard to know which verb should be used. But some examples of what could be filled in the blank to make a complete sentence:

* they "left" out just now
* they "went" out just now
* they "stepped" out just now
* they "logged" out just now
* they "checked" out just now

If you provide more context, I could give you a more specific answer.
